                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent"> In 
                                403/4
                                A. Gr.
                                        720
                             Mar Diogenis
                             began to build  the House of  Mar Barlāhā
                                .  <a href="/8559-244" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> On 
                                4 September A. D.
                                        525
                                4 Elul A. Gr.
                                        836
                             they moved the body of  Asclepius  from
                                 Antioch 
                            to  Edessa 
                            where he was buried alongside  Nonos  in the
                                 the House of
                                     Mar Barlāhā
                                .  <a href="/8559-484" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent"> In 
                                December A. D.
                                        532
                                Kānun I A. Gr.
                                        844
                             Andreos
                             died and was buried in the  the House of  Mar Barlāhā
                                 alongside the bones of  Mar Nonos  and
                                 Mar Asclepius
                             <a href="/8559-512" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
